From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 19:43:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] perftest: replace deprecated OpenMP 'master' with 'masked'

The 'master' construct was deprecated in OpenMP 5.1 in favor of
'masked'. GCC 14+ emits -Wdeprecated-openmp for it, which becomes a
hard error under UCX's -Werror build, breaking the build of
ucx_perftest:

    src/tools/perf/perftest.c:261:11: error: 'master' construct
        deprecated since OpenMP 5.1, use 'masked'
        [-Werror=deprecated-openmp]

Use 'masked filter(0)' when the implementation advertises OpenMP
>= 5.1 (_OPENMP >= 202011), and keep 'master' for older OpenMP
runtimes so we do not break GCC/Clang versions that don't know
the 'masked' directive yet. Both occurrences in perftest.c are
patched (sock_rte_barrier and the HAVE_MPI mpi_rte_barrier path).

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
---
 src/tools/perf/perftest.c | 12 ++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/tools/perf/perftest.c b/src/tools/perf/perftest.c
--- a/src/tools/perf/perftest.c
+++ b/src/tools/perf/perftest.c
@@ -258,7 +258,11 @@ static void sock_rte_barrier(void *rte_group, void (*progress)(void *arg),
 {
 #if _OPENMP
 #  pragma omp barrier
-#  pragma omp master
+#  if _OPENMP >= 202011
+#    pragma omp masked filter(0)
+#  else
+#    pragma omp master
+#  endif
 #endif
   {
     sock_rte_group_t *group = rte_group;
@@ -592,7 +596,11 @@ static void mpi_rte_barrier(void *rte_group, void (*progress)(void *arg),
 
 #pragma omp barrier
 
-#pragma omp master
+#if defined(_OPENMP) && _OPENMP >= 202011
+#  pragma omp masked filter(0)
+#else
+#  pragma omp master
+#endif
   {
     /*
      * Naive non-blocking barrier implementation over send/recv, to call user
